{"title_page": "Ryuji Imaichi", "text_new": "{{Infobox singer\n| name                = Ryuji Imaichi\n| image               =Imaichi Ryuji from \"That Moment, My Heart Cried\" at Opening Ceremony of the Tokyo International Film Festival 2019 (49013775057).jpg\n| caption             =Imaichi in 2019\n| background          = solo_singer\n| native_name         = \u4eca\u5e02\u9686\u4e8c \n| native_name_lang    = ja\n| birth_name          = \n| birth_date          = {{Birth date and age|1986|09|02}}\n| birth_place         = [[Kyoto Prefecture]], Japan\n| occupation = {{flatlist|\n[[Singing|Singer]]\n[[actor]]\n}}\n| module = {{Infobox musical artist | embed = yes\n| background          = solo_singer\n| instrument          = [[Singing|Vocals]]\n| genre  = [[J-pop]]\n| years_active  = 2010\u2013present\n| label  = [[Rhythm Zone]]\n| associated_acts  = {{flat list|\n*[[Sandaime J Soul Brothers from Exile Tribe|Sandaime J Soul Brothers]]\n*[[Exile Tribe]]}}\n| website   =  {{official website|URL=https://www.ldh.co.jp/eng/management/imaichi/}}\n}}\n}}\n{{nihongo|'''Ryuji Imaichi'''|\u4eca\u5e02 \u9686\u4e8c|Imaichi Ry\u016bji|born September 2, 1986, in [[Kyoto Prefecture]], Japan}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jsoulb.jp/profile/ryuji.php|title=Official profile|accessdate=2015-09-01}}</ref> is a Japanese singer and actor. He is a vocalist of the [[J-pop]] dance and vocal group [[Sandaime J Soul Brothers from Exile Tribe]]. He joined the group after winning the ''VOCAL BATTLE AUDITION 2'' alongside [[Hiroomi Tosaka]].<ref name=\":4\" /> As a member of [[Sandaime J Soul Brothers]], he has received the [[Japan Record Awards]] twice.<ref name=\":4\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.ldh.co.jp/eng/management/jsoulbrothers/|title=J SOUL BROTHERS III from EXILE TRIBE {{!}} MANAGEMENT {{!}} LDH|website=www.ldh.co.jp|access-date=2019-12-31}}</ref> Since 2014, he has become the Thursday host for [[J-Wave|J\u2212WAVE]]'s \"SPARK\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.j-wave.co.jp/blog/spark/2014/10/spark-1.html|title=SPARK : J-WAVE 81.3 FM RADIO|website=www.j-wave.co.jp|access-date=2019-12-31}}</ref><ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.ldh.co.jp/eng/management/imaichi/|title=RYUJI IMAICHI {{!}} MANAGEMENT {{!}} LDH|website=www.ldh.co.jp|access-date=2019-12-31}}</ref>\n\nHe made his solo debut in January 2018 with the digital single \"ONE DAY\", while remaining a member of [[Sandaime J Soul Brothers from Exile Tribe|Sandaime J Soul Brothers]]. For his solo activities he uses his birth name stylized as RYUJI IMAICHI.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\nHe debuted as an actor in 2019 in short film ''On The Way'' of the drama anthology ''Sono Shunkan, Boku wa Nakitaku Natta -Cinema Fighters project-.''<ref name=\":0\" />\n==Early life==\nRyuji Imaichi was born on September 2, 1986 in [[Kyoto Prefecture]], Japan, but was raised in [[Kawasaki, Kanagawa|Kawasaki, Kanagawa Prefecture]].<ref name=\":0\" /> He played [[baseball]] in elementary school and junior high school as a [[pitcher]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.j-wave.fm/news/2018/09/830jsb.html|title=\u4e09\u4ee3\u76eeJSB\u30fb\u4eca\u5e02\u9686\u4e8c\u3001\u5c0f\u5b66\u751f\u306e\u3053\u308d\u306e\u201c\u75db\u3044\u601d\u3044\u51fa\u201d\u3068\u306f\uff1f {{!}} J-WAVE NEWS|website=news.j-wave.fm|language=ja|access-date=2020-01-05}}</ref> According to himself, he was a rebellious teenager and dropped out of high school at the age of 16. He then started to do different part-time jobs, including dish washing at a [[ramen]] shop, and spent his wages playing with the [[pachinko]] and [[Slot machine|slot machines]] in his free time. After a year and a half, one of his friends, a [[construction worker]] in the neighboring city, invited Imaichi to work together at his company and become a construction worker too. Imaichi chose to specialize in pressure [[welding]] since the job paid a higher salary than for a normal construction worker. He achieved to earn all the required licenses to become a welder.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite book|title=Timeless Time|last=Imaichi|first=Ryuji|publisher=Gentosha|year=2018|isbn=978-4344032422|location=|pages=}}</ref><ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=https://hochi.news/articles/20180119-OHT1T50120.html|title=\u4e09\u4ee3\u76ee\uff2a\uff33\uff22\u30fb\u4eca\u5e02\u9686\u4e8c\u3001\u5922\uff0d\uff21\uff34\uff33\uff35\uff33\uff28\uff29\u306e\u3088\u3046\u306b\u5358\u72ec\u30c9\u30fc\u30e0\u516c\u6f14|date=2018-01-20|website=\u30b9\u30dd\u30fc\u30c4\u5831\u77e5|language=ja|access-date=2020-01-05}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sponichi.co.jp/entertainment/news/2018/06/01/kiji/20180601s00041000195000c.html|title=\u4e09\u4ee3\u76ee\uff2e\uff21\uff2f\uff34\uff2f\u3001\u6bcd\u306e\u9b54\u5973\u30b3\u30b9\u30d7\u30ec\u306b\u9a5a\u304c\u304f\u3000\u4eca\u5e02\u306f\u300c\u6016\u304b\u3063\u305f\u89aa\u65b9\u304c\u2026\u300d|last=|first=|date=|website=www.sponichi.co.jp|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-01-06}}</ref>\n\nImaichi became a big fan of [[Atsushi (musician)|Atsushi]] as early as 2000 when he saw him taking part in the [[Asayan]] talent search TV show. When Atsushi debuted as the vocalist of [[Exile (Japanese band)|Exile]] later on, Imaichi quickly became a big fan of the group and learned to sing their songs. However, he did not initially have the dream of becoming a singer. In 2006, his then girlfriend encouraged him to participate in the ''Vocal Battle Audition 2006: Asian Dream'', an audition to find a new vocalist for Exile. He passed the first round without much preparation but failed to pass the second round. Despite his loss, he became serious about pursuing a career as a singer, and he was determined to get revenge for his failure. From that point on he started attending vocal training lessons at the Vocal Academy of Tokyo at nights, after a full day of work as a construction worker.<ref name=\":1\" /><ref name=\":2\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://wezz-y.com/archives/55074|title=\u4e09\u4ee3\u76eeJSB\u4eca\u5e02\u9686\u4e8c\u306e\u30bd\u30ed\u6d3b\u52d5\u304c\u7d76\u597d\u8abf\uff01 \u61a7\u308c\u306eATSUSHI\u3078\u306e\u601d\u3044\u300c\u306a\u308a\u305f\u304f\u3066\u306a\u308a\u305f\u304f\u3066\u2026\u300d|website=wezzy\uff5c\u30a6\u30a7\u30b8\u30fc|language=ja|access-date=2020-01-05}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.voat.co.jp/artist/|title=\u3010\u30c7\u30d3\u30e5\u30fc\u5b9f\u7e3e\u3011\u30dc\u30a4\u30b9\u30c8\u30ec\u30fc\u30cb\u30f3\u30b0\u306f\u30dc\u30fc\u30ab\u30eb\u30b9\u30af\u30fc\u30ebVOAT\uff5c\u6771\u4eac\u30fb\u540d\u53e4\u5c4b\u30fb\u798f\u5ca1|last=\u30dc\u30fc\u30ab\u30eb\u30b9\u30af\u30fc\u30ebVOAT|website=www.voat.co.jp|language=ja|access-date=2020-01-05}}</ref>\n\nIn 2009, he won runner up Grand Prix in the artist category of the ''[[Avex Group|avex]] WORLD AUDITION 2008'',<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.avex.co.jp/html/upload_file/top_01/7860_2010021619551502_P01_.pdf|title=\u300cavex WORLD AUDITION 2008\u300d\u6700\u7d42\u9078\u8003\u7d50\u679c\u306b\u3064\u3044\u3066|last=|first=|date=2009-02-23|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-01-04}}</ref> and started being enrolled in the Avex Artist Academy as a scholarship student. From 2006 to 2010, he took part in more than 100 different auditions.<ref name=\":1\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.m-on-music.jp/0000252051/|title=\u4e09\u4ee3\u76eeJSB\u30fb\u4eca\u5e02\u9686\u4e8c\u3001\u81ea\u8eab\u306e\u201c\u30aa\u30fc\u30c7\u30a3\u30b7\u30e7\u30f3\u6642\u4ee3\u201d\u306b\u3064\u3044\u3066\u8a00\u53ca\u3002\u300cJSB\u306b\u5165\u308b\u524d\u306b\u3001100\u500b\u3050\u3089\u3044\u53d7\u3051\u3066\u307e\u3059\u300d|last=MUSIC(\u30a8\u30e0\u30aa\u30f3\u30df\u30e5\u30fc\u30b8\u30c3\u30af)|first=\u97f3\u697dWEB\u30e1\u30c7\u30a3\u30a2 M.-ON!|website=\u97f3\u697dWEB\u30e1\u30c7\u30a3\u30a2 M-ON! MUSIC(\u30a8\u30e0\u30aa\u30f3\u30df\u30e5\u30fc\u30b8\u30c3\u30af)|language=ja|access-date=2020-01-05}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\nIn February 2010, Imaichi participated in the ''Vocal Battle Audition 2: ~Yume o Motta Wakamono-tachi e~''. As he turned 24 that year, he considered this chance as the last try for his dream to become a professional singer. He passed the first round and met [[Hiroomi Tosaka]] in the second round. They considered each other to be strong competitors after seeing their performances for the first round on Sh\u00fbkan Exile's coverage of the audition. As Imaichi and Tosaka both were selected as two of the ten finalists after the third round, it was announced that the two winners of ''Vocal Battle Audition 2'' would become the vocalists of the new dance and vocal group [[Sandaime J Soul Brothers]]. On September 15, 2010, the final round of the audition was held at [[Akasaka Blitz]] music venue and Imaichi won the audition alongside [[Hiroomi Tosaka]]. The two officially became the vocalists of [[Sandaime J Soul Brothers]]. A few days later, as they finished recording Sandaime's first single, the seven members of the group met each other for the first time.<ref name=\":1\" /><ref>J Soul Brothers Document(Special Movie) in Album J Soul Brothers, released in 25 February 2009.</ref> On September 27, Imaichi and Tosaka made their first public appearance as singers during the ''Fantasy Goya-sai: Exile Tamash\u012b'' (FANTASY\u5f8c\u591c\u796d\uff5eEXILE\u9b42\uff5e; ''FANTASY Late Night Festival ~EXILE Soul~'') live performance from [[Exile (Japanese band)|Exile]] at [[Toyota Stadium]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/news/music/80467/full/|title=\u65b0\u30e1\u30f3\u30d0\u30fc\u6c7a\u5b9a\uff01\u4e09\u4ee3\u76eeJ Soul Brothers\u304a\u62ab\u9732\u76ee|accessdate=2015-09-01}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://m.ex-m.jp/static_renew_before/sppg/extribe2012/whats/3rd_jsb|title=Profile-Sandaime J Soul Brothers|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-01-04}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tokyohive.com/article/2010/09/exile-members-3rd-generation-dance-unit-announced|title=EXILE members' 3rd generation dance unit announced {{!}} tokyohive.com|website=www.tokyohive.com|language=en|access-date=2020-01-05}}</ref> On November 10, Sandaime J Soul Brothers with the single \"Best Friend's Girl\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.oricon.co.jp/news/80835/full/|title=\u4e09\u4ee3\u76eeJSoulBrothers\u3001\u30c7\u30d3\u30e5\u30fc\u30b7\u30f3\u30b0\u30eb\u304cCM\u30bd\u30f3\u30b0\u306b\u6c7a\u5b9a|website=ORICON NEWS|access-date=2020-01-05}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.oricon.co.jp/news/81923/full/|title=\u4e09\u4ee3\u76eeJSB\u3001\u30c7\u30d3\u30e5\u30fc\u30a4\u30d9\u30f3\u30c8\u306b1\u4e076000\u4eba|website=ORICON NEWS|access-date=2020-01-05}}</ref>\n\nFrom November 2012 to March,2013, Imaichi appeared in TBS's music variety show ''EX-LOUNGE''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tbs.co.jp/ex-lounge/|title=EX-LOUNGE|last=TBS|first=|date=|website=TBS|language=ja|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-01-05}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://m.ex-m.jp/static_renew_before/artist/exile/tv/exlounge/index|title=EX-LOUNGE|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-01-04}}</ref> In 2013, he sang [[Kimigayo|the national anthem of Japan]] on the stage of the [[International Boxing Federation|IBF]] World Boxing Championship held in [[Kagawa Prefecture]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://boxmob.jp/sp/news/index.html?nid=7536&n=1|title=\u3010\u30dc\u30af\u30e2\u30d0\u30cb\u30e5\u30fc\u30b9\u3011\u5927\u6bc5\u306e\u4e16\u754c\u6226\u3092\u5f8c\u62bc\u3057 2013.8.28|website=\u30dc\u30af\u30b7\u30f3\u30b0\u30e2\u30d0\u30a4\u30eb|language=ja|access-date=2020-01-05}}</ref>\n\nIn 2014, Imaichi composed the lyrics for Sandaime J Soul Brothers' song \"PRIDE\", which was his first attempt at lyric composition.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.j-wave.fm/news/2016/09/jsb-5.html|title=\u4e09\u4ee3\u76eeJSB\u4eca\u5e02\u9686\u4e8c\u304c\u5c0a\u656c\u3059\u308b\u4f5c\u8a5e\u5bb6\u306f\uff1f {{!}} J-WAVE NEWS|website=news.j-wave.fm|language=ja|access-date=2020-01-05}}</ref> Since October 2014, he has become the Thursday host for [[J-Wave|J\u2212WAVE]]'s \"SPARK\". On the radio, Imaichi shares the songs and musicians that he loves with his listeners, and he introduced [[Brian McKnight]] on his very first broadcast.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.j-wave.co.jp/blog/spark/2014/10/spark_1.html|title=SPARK : J-WAVE 81.3 FM RADIO|website=www.j-wave.co.jp|access-date=2020-01-05}}</ref>\n\nIn 2015, he released his first solo song \"All LOVE\" as part of Sandaime J Soul Brothers' album ''[[Planet Seven|PLANET SEVEN]]'' under the name of the group. Furthermore, he was featured on [[Dance Earth Party|DANCE EARTH PARTY]]'s [[Cover version|cover]] of \"Beautiful Name\" originally by [[Godiego]], which was released on August 5.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://e-talentbank.co.jp/news/11987/|title=\u4e09\u4ee3\u76eeJSB\u30fb\u4eca\u5e02\u9686\u4e8c\u304c\u53c2\u52a0\uff01\u300cBEAUTIFUL NAME feat.\u4eca\u5e02\u9686\u4e8c from \u4e09\u4ee3\u76ee J Soul Brothers\u300dLive Video\u304c\u5148\u884c\u914d\u4fe1\u958b\u59cb\uff5cE-TALENTBANK co.,ltd.|website=E-TALENTBANK co.,ltd.|language=ja|access-date=2020-01-05}}</ref> He also featured on [[Crystal Kay]]'s Japanese cover of \"[[Very Special (song)|Very Special]]\" by [[Debra Laws]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://natalie.mu/music/news/169206|title=Crystal Kay\u00d7\u4eca\u5e02\u9686\u4e8c\u3001\u30c7\u30e5\u30a8\u30c3\u30c8\u30b7\u30fc\u30f3\u53ce\u3081\u305f\u300cVery Special\u300d\u6620\u50cf\u516c\u958b|last=Inc|first=Natasha|website=\u97f3\u697d\u30ca\u30bf\u30ea\u30fc|language=ja|access-date=2020-01-05}}</ref>\n\nIn 2016, Sandaime J Soul Brothers released a documentary about themselves, ''Born in the EXILE''. The theme song of the documentary had the same title as the film and Ryuji Imaichi and [[Hiroomi Tosaka]] composed the lyrics of the song together to express the \"soul\" of the group.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cinemacafe.net/article/2016/02/12/37828.html|title=\u767b\u5742\u5e83\u81e3\uff06\u4eca\u5e02\u9686\u4e8c\u306b\u3088\u308b\u65b0\u66f2\u6b4c\u8a5e\u306bELLY\u611f\u52d5\uff01\u300c\u30a2\u30ab\u30da\u30e9\u3067\u8e0a\u3063\u3066\u307f\u305f\u3044\u300d|website=cinemacafe.net|language=ja|access-date=2020-01-05}}</ref> In the same year, Imaichi also released his first solo song under his own name titled \"Forever Young At Heart\" in ''HiGH & LOW ORIGINAL BEST ALBUM'', and the song was used as part of the soundtrack for the TV shows and films of the [[:ja:HiGH&LOW\u301cTHE_STORY_OF_S.W.O.R.D.\u301c|''High & Low'']] franchise, an action and music franchise produced by [[LDH (company)|LDH]].<ref name=\":3\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.m-on-music.jp/0000128589/|title=\u300cROAD TO HiGH\uff06LOW\u300d\u30c6\u30fc\u30de\u66f2\u30fb\u4eca\u5e02\u9686\u4e8c\u300cFOREVER YOUNG AT HEART\u300d\u30b9\u30da\u30b7\u30e3\u30eb\u30c8\u30ec\u30fc\u30e9\u30fc\u89e3\u7981|last=MUSIC(\u30a8\u30e0\u30aa\u30f3\u30df\u30e5\u30fc\u30b8\u30c3\u30af)|first=\u97f3\u697dWEB\u30e1\u30c7\u30a3\u30a2 M.-ON!|website=\u97f3\u697dWEB\u30e1\u30c7\u30a3\u30a2 M-ON! MUSIC(\u30a8\u30e0\u30aa\u30f3\u30df\u30e5\u30fc\u30b8\u30c3\u30af)|language=ja|access-date=2020-01-05}}</ref>\n\nIn September 2017, as Sandaime J Soul Brothers' member [[Kenjiro Yamashita]] starred in dTV\u00d7FOD's romance drama ''Love or Not'', Imaichi was appointed as the host of a music television program titled ''Love or Not\u266a'', which was part of the ''Love or Not'' project. The show ended in February 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://fod.fujitv.co.jp/s/genre/music/ser0133/|title=LOVE or NOT \u266a|website=FOD|language=ja|access-date=2020-01-05}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.m-on-music.jp/0000255739/|title=\u4e09\u4ee3\u76eeJSB\u30fb\u4eca\u5e02\u9686\u4e8c\u3001\u300eLOVE or NOT\u266a\u300f\u6700\u7d42\u56de\u3067\u30bd\u30ed\u66f2\u3092\u71b1\u5531\uff01\u300c\u3059\u3054\u304f\u523a\u6fc0\u3092\u53d7\u3051\u307e\u3057\u305f\u3057\u3001\u52c9\u5f37\u306b\u306a\u308a\u307e\u3057\u305f\u300d|last=MUSIC(\u30a8\u30e0\u30aa\u30f3\u30df\u30e5\u30fc\u30b8\u30c3\u30af)|first=\u97f3\u697dWEB\u30e1\u30c7\u30a3\u30a2 M.-ON!|website=\u97f3\u697dWEB\u30e1\u30c7\u30a3\u30a2 M-ON! MUSIC(\u30a8\u30e0\u30aa\u30f3\u30df\u30e5\u30fc\u30b8\u30c3\u30af)|language=ja|access-date=2020-01-05}}</ref>\n\nOn January 12, 2018, while remaining a member of Sandaime J Soul Brothers, Imaichi made his solo debut with the digital single \"ONE DAY\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.oricon.co.jp/news/2104082/full/|title=\u3010\u30aa\u30ea\u30b3\u30f3\u3011\u4e09\u4ee3\u76eeJSB\u4eca\u5e02\u9686\u4e8c\u3001\u30bd\u30ed\u7b2c1\u5f3e\u914d\u4fe1\u30b7\u30f3\u30b0\u30eb\u304cDL1\u4f4d|website=ORICON NEWS|access-date=2019-09-13}}</ref> The single immediately took first place on [[Oricon]]'s weekly digital single chart.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.oricon.co.jp/news/2104238/full/|title=1/22\u4ed8\u9031\u9593\u30c7\u30b8\u30bf\u30eb\u30b7\u30f3\u30b0\u30eb\uff08\u5358\u66f2\uff09\u30e9\u30f3\u30ad\u30f3\u30b01\u4f4d\u306fRYUJIIMAICHI\u306e\u300cONEDAY\u300d|website=ORICON NEWS|access-date=2019-09-13}}</ref> He continued to release more digital singles throughout the year, such as \"Angel\" on February 16,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://natalie.mu/music/news/270225|title=\u4e09\u4ee3\u76eeJSB\u4eca\u5e02\u9686\u4e8c\u3001\u30bd\u30ed\u7b2c2\u5f3e\u697d\u66f2\u300cAngel\u300d\u30df\u30e5\u30fc\u30b8\u30c3\u30af\u30d3\u30c7\u30aa\u516c\u958b|last=|first=|date=|website=natalie|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> \"Thank you\" on March 16 and \"Alter Ego\" on April 20.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://m.tribe-m.jp/news/detail?news_id=15232|title=\u3010Music Video\u89e3\u7981!!\u30114/20(Fri)Release!!RYUJI IMAICHI4\u30f6\u6708\u9023\u7d9aDigital Single\u7b2c4\u5f3e\u300eAlter Ego\u300f {{!}} NEWS|website=EXILE TRIBE mobile|language=ja|access-date=2020-01-05}}</ref> He also befriended his longtime idol [[Brian McKnight|Brian Mcknight]], and the two collaborated to produce Imaichi's song \"Thank you\" when Imaichi stayed at Mcknight's home.<ref name=\":2\" /> Furthermore, Imaichi released his first photo essay titled ''TIMELESS TIME'' on March 26, which was produced by American Artist [[Daniel Arsham]].<ref name=\":5\">{{Cite web|url=https://mdpr.jp/interview/detail/1755642|title=\uff1c\u4e09\u4ee3\u76eeJSB\u4eca\u5e02\u9686\u4e8c\u30a4\u30f3\u30bf\u30d3\u30e5\u30fc\uff1e\u300c\u5168\u3066\u3092\u3055\u3089\u3051\u51fa\u3059\u65b9\u304c\u3044\u3044\u300d\u2015\u30bd\u30ed\u3068\u3057\u3066\u306e\u201c\u81ea\u5206\u201d\u3068\u306f\uff1f\u30c0\u30cb\u30a8\u30eb\u30fb\u30a2\u30fc\u30b7\u30e3\u30e0\u3068\u306e\u30b3\u30e9\u30dc\u304c\u523a\u6fc0\u306b\u3010\u524d\u7de8\u3011 - \u30e2\u30c7\u30eb\u30d7\u30ec\u30b9|website=\u30e2\u30c7\u30eb\u30d7\u30ec\u30b9 - \u30e9\u30a4\u30d5\u30b9\u30bf\u30a4\u30eb\u30fb\u30d5\u30a1\u30c3\u30b7\u30e7\u30f3\u30a8\u30f3\u30bf\u30e1\u30cb\u30e5\u30fc\u30b9|language=ja|access-date=2020-01-05}}</ref> After releasing his first solo album ''LIGHT>DARKNESS'' on August 1,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://natalie.mu/music/news/287885|title=\u4e09\u4ee3\u76eeJSB\u4eca\u5e02\u9686\u4e8c\uff06\u767b\u5742\u5e83\u81e3\u3001\u30c4\u30a2\u30fc\u3068\u9023\u52d5\u3057\u305f\u30b3\u30f3\u30d7\u30ea\u30fc\u30c8\u30a2\u30eb\u30d0\u30e0\u767a\u58f2|last=|first=|date=|website=natalie|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> he concluded his solo activities in 2018 by going on his first tour titled ''Ryuji Imaichi Live Tour 2018 \"Light>Darkness\"''  from August 11 to December 24.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://natalie.mu/music/news/280684|title=\u4e09\u4ee3\u76eeJSB\u4eca\u5e02\u9686\u4e8c\uff06\u767b\u5742\u5e83\u81e3\u3001\u30bd\u30ed\u30c4\u30a2\u30fc\u65e5\u7a0b\u660e\u3089\u304b\u306b|last=|first=|date=|website=natalie|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> Brian Mcknight took part in Imaichi's show in [[Saitama Super Arena]] as a guest star, and the two performed Brian McKnight's \"[[Back at One (song)|Back At One]]\" together.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.daily.co.jp/gossip/2018/12/03/0011871847.shtml|title=\u4eca\u5e02\u9686\u4e8c \u6d99\u306e\u30b3\u30e9\u30dc\u5531 \u30d6\u30e9\u30a4\u30a2\u30f3\u30fb\u30de\u30c3\u30af\u30ca\u30a4\u30c8\u3068/\u30c7\u30a4\u30ea\u30fc\u30b9\u30dd\u30fc\u30c4 online|website=\u30c7\u30a4\u30ea\u30fc\u30b9\u30dd\u30fc\u30c4 online|language=ja|access-date=2020-01-05}}</ref>\n\nPrior to the release of the live footage from his first solo tour on March 6, 2019, Imaichi released his 5th digital single \"Yoake Mae / Kore ga Unmei Nara\" (\u591c\u660e\u3051\u524d / \u3053\u308c\u304c\u904b\u547d\u306a\u3089; ''Before Dawn / If This is Destiny'') on February 15.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://natalie.mu/music/news/319856|title=\u4e09\u4ee3\u76eeJSB\u4eca\u5e02\u9686\u4e8c\u3001\u30e9\u30a4\u30d6\u6620\u50cf\u4f5c\u54c1\u767a\u58f2\u306b\u5148\u99c6\u3051\u65b0\u66f2\u914d\u4fe1\u30ea\u30ea\u30fc\u30b9|last=|first=|date=|website=natalie|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> Furthermore, he made his acting debut in fall 2019 in the short film ''Uta Monogatari -CINEMA FIGHTERS project-''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.oricon.co.jp/news/2146583/full/|title=\u4eca\u5e02\u9686\u4e8c\u3001\u4ff3\u512a\u30c7\u30d3\u30e5\u30fc\u521d\u65e5\u306b20\u30c6\u30a4\u30af\u300c\u5fc3\u6298\u308c\u305d\u3046\u3067\u3057\u305f\u300d|website=ORICON NEWS|access-date=2020-01-05}}</ref> It was also announced that he would release his first physical single \"RILY\" on October 30. Furthermore, he appeared on the cover of ''[[Anan (magazine)|anan]]''<nowiki/>'s issue 2175 at the end of the year, making it first solo magazine cover in his career.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://natalie.mu/music/news/353094|title=\u4e09\u4ee3\u76eeJSB\u4eca\u5e02\u9686\u4e8c\u300canan\u300d\u306e\u201c\u7d46\u201d\u7279\u96c6\u3067\u8868\u7d19\u98fe\u308b\u3001\u30e9\u30f3\u30da\u3068\u30d0\u30ea\u30dc\u3082\u767b\u5834|last=Inc|first=Natasha|website=\u97f3\u697d\u30ca\u30bf\u30ea\u30fc|language=ja|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://mdpr.jp/news/detail/1887993|title=\u4e09\u4ee3\u76eeJSB\u4eca\u5e02\u9686\u4e8c\u300canan\u300d\u30bd\u30ed\u521d\u8868\u7d19 \u30b0\u30eb\u30fc\u30d7\u306e\u7d46\u8a9e\u308b - \u30e2\u30c7\u30eb\u30d7\u30ec\u30b9|website=\u30e2\u30c7\u30eb\u30d7\u30ec\u30b9 - \u30e9\u30a4\u30d5\u30b9\u30bf\u30a4\u30eb\u30fb\u30d5\u30a1\u30c3\u30b7\u30e7\u30f3\u30a8\u30f3\u30bf\u30e1\u30cb\u30e5\u30fc\u30b9|language=ja|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n\nOn January 15, 2020, Imaichi released his second studio album ''ZONE OF GOLD'' <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://m.tribe-m.jp/news/detail?news_id=21030|title=2020.1.15(Wed)RYUJI IMAICHI \u30cb\u30e5\u30fc\u30fb\u30a2\u30eb\u30d0\u30e0\u300eZONE OF GOLD\u300f\u30ea\u30ea\u30fc\u30b9\u6c7a\u5b9a!! {{!}} NEWS|website=EXILE TRIBE mobile|language=ja|access-date=2019-11-23}}</ref>.  In January and February, Imaichi and [[Hiroomi Tosaka]] held their first joint dome tour titled ''LDH PERFECT YEAR 2020 SPECIAL SHOWCASE RYUJI IMAICHI / HIROOMI TOSAKA''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://natalie.mu/music/news/348599|title=\u300cLDH PERFECT YEAR 2020\u300d\u3067EXILE\u306e\u30d9\u30b9\u30c8\u30e9\u30a4\u30d6\u3001\u4eca\u5e02\uff06\u767b\u5742\u3089\u306e\u30e9\u30a4\u30d6\u958b\u50ac\u6c7a\u5b9a\uff08\u52d5\u753b\u3042\u308a\uff09|last=Inc|first=Natasha|website=\u97f3\u697d\u30ca\u30bf\u30ea\u30fc|language=ja|access-date=2020-01-05}}</ref> In January, Imaichi was also appointed as the 30th-anniversary ambassador of [[:ja:\u3058\u3083\u3089\u3093|Jalan magazine]], one of Japan's largest travel magazines.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://spice.eplus.jp/articles/262715|title=\u4e09\u4ee3\u76ee J SOUL BROTHERS \u4eca\u5e02\u9686\u4e8c\u304c\u300e\u3058\u3083\u3089\u3093\u300f30\u5468\u5e74\u30a2\u30f3\u30d0\u30b5\u30c0\u30fc\u306b\u3001\u88b4\u59ff\u3067\u8868\u7d19\u98fe\u308b {{!}} SPICE - \u30a8\u30f3\u30bf\u30e1\u7279\u5316\u578b\u60c5\u5831\u30e1\u30c7\u30a3\u30a2 \u30b9\u30d1\u30a4\u30b9|website=SPICE\uff08\u30b9\u30d1\u30a4\u30b9\uff09\uff5c\u30a8\u30f3\u30bf\u30e1\u7279\u5316\u578b\u60c5\u5831\u30e1\u30c7\u30a3\u30a2 \u30b9\u30d1\u30a4\u30b9|access-date=2020-01-05}}</ref>\n<br />\n\n== Personal Life ==\nImaichi has a brother and a sister. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.j-wave.fm/news/2019/04/411-jsb.html|title=\u4e09\u4ee3\u76eeJSB\u30fb\u4eca\u5e02\u9686\u4e8c\u304c\u3001\u81ea\u8eab\u306e\u5144\u30fb\u59b9\u3068\u4f3c\u3066\u3044\u308b\u3068\u611f\u3058\u308b\u90e8\u5206\u300c\u3061\u3087\u3063\u3068\u5acc\u3067\u3057\u305f\u306d\uff08\u7b11\uff09\u300d {{!}} J-WAVE NEWS|website=news.j-wave.fm|language=ja|access-date=2020-01-05}}</ref>\n\nHe has been a fan of  [[Atsushi (musician)|Atsushi]] since he was a teenager, and is a big fan of [[Brian McKnight|Brian Mcknight]]. Both artists deeply influenced his music style.<ref name=\":2\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.news-postseven.com/archives/20150217_303889.html|title=\u4e09\u4ee3\u76eeJ\u4eca\u5e02\u3068\u5ca9\u7530 Xmas\u306b3\u65e5\u9023\u7d9a\u3067\u713c\u304d\u8089\u30c7\u30fc\u30c8\u3057\u305f\u3053\u3068\u3082|website=NEWS\u30dd\u30b9\u30c8\u30bb\u30d6\u30f3|language=ja|access-date=2020-01-06}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.billboard-japan.com/special/detail/2608|title=\u30d6\u30e9\u30a4\u30a2\u30f3\u30fb\u30de\u30c3\u30af\u30ca\u30a4\u30c8\u6765\u65e5\u8a18\u5ff5\u7279\u96c6 \uff5e27\u5e74\u9593\u3001\u30bd\u30ed\u3067\u30ad\u30e3\u30ea\u30a2\u3092\u7a4d\u3080R&B\u30b7\u30f3\u30ac\u30fc\u306e\u300c\u3044\u307e\u300d {{!}} Special|website=Billboard JAPAN|language=ja|access-date=2020-01-06}}</ref> He is often compared to [[Atsushi (musician)|Atsushi]], for his resemblance to him while wearing sunglasses.\n\nAs a baseball lover, he built up a baseball team called NAKAMEGURO RYUJI 'S inside [[LDH (company)|LDH]], with the company's staff members and artists as its players and himself as the coach.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://mdpr.jp/news/detail/1871338|title=\u4e09\u4ee3\u76eeJSB\u4eca\u5e02\u9686\u4e8c\u201c\u76e3\u7763\u201d\u306e\u65b0\u5165\u90e8\u54e1\u52e7\u8a98\u30b9\u30bf\u30fc\u30c8 - \u30e2\u30c7\u30eb\u30d7\u30ec\u30b9|website=\u30e2\u30c7\u30eb\u30d7\u30ec\u30b9 - \u30e9\u30a4\u30d5\u30b9\u30bf\u30a4\u30eb\u30fb\u30d5\u30a1\u30c3\u30b7\u30e7\u30f3\u30a8\u30f3\u30bf\u30e1\u30cb\u30e5\u30fc\u30b9|language=ja|access-date=2020-01-06}}</ref> \n\n==Discography==\n{{about||his appearances with Sandaime J Soul Brothers|Sandaime J Soul Brothers}}\n\n=== Studio albums ===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\"| Title\n! rowspan=\"2\"| Details\n! colspan=\"1\"| Peak chart positions\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Oricon Albums Chart|JPN]]<br /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.oricon.co.jp/prof/587279/rank/|title=\u4eca\u5e02\u9686\u4e8c\u306e\u58f2\u4e0a\u30e9\u30f3\u30ad\u30f3\u30b0|trans-title=Ryuji Imaichi Sales Ranking|publisher=[[Oricon]]|accessdate=November 6, 2019|language=Japanese}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''Light>Darkness''\n|\n* Released: August 1, 2018\n* Label: [[Rhythm Zone]]\n* Formats: CD, CD/DVD, CD/Blu-ray\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|2\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''Zone of Gold''\n|\n* Released: January 15, 2020\n* Label: [[Rhythm Zone]]\n* Formats: CD, CD/DVD, CD/Blu-ray\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|4\n|}\n\n=== Singles ===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\"| Title\n! rowspan=\"2\"| Year\n! colspan=\"2\"| Peak chart positions\n! rowspan=\"2\"| Certifications\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Oricon Singles Chart|JPN<br />Oricon]]<br /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.oricon.co.jp/rank/js/w/2019-11-11/|title=\u9031\u9593 CD\u30b7\u30f3\u30b0\u30eb\u30e9\u30f3\u30ad\u30f3\u30b0 2019\u5e7411\u670811\u65e5\u4ed8|trans-title=Weekly CD Single Ranking for November 11, 2019|publisher=Oricon|accessdate=November 6, 2019|language=Japanese}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Billboard Japan Hot 100|JPN<br />Hot<br />100]]\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|\"RILY\"\n|2019\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|2\n|{{TBA}}\n|{{TBA}}\n|}\n\n===Digital singles===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Year\n!Title\n!Release Date\n!Album\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\" |2018\n|One Day\n|January 12\n| rowspan=\"4\" |''LIGHT>DARKNESS''\n|-\n|Angel\n|February 16\n|-\n|Thank You\n|March 16\n|-\n|Alter Ego\n|April 20\n|-\n|2019\n|Yoake Mae / Kore ga Unmei Nara\n|February 15\n|\n|}\n\n=== Other Solo Songs ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Year\n!Title\n!Release Date\n!Album\n|-\n|2015\n|All LOVE\n|January 28\n|[[Sandaime J Soul Brothers]] \"[[Planet Seven|''PLANET SEVEN'']]\"\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |2016\n|Over & Over\n|March 30\n|Sandaime J Soul Brothers \"[[The JSB Legacy|THE JSB LEGACY]]\"\n|-\n|FOREVER YOUNG AT HEART\n|June 15\n|V.A.\"HiGH&LOW ORIGINAL BEST ALBUM\"\n|-\n|}\n\n=== Participating works ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Year\n! Title\n! Artist\n!Recording\n! Notes\n! Ref.\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |2015\n| BEAUTIFUL NAME ||[[Dance Earth Party]]\n|''I''|| Cover by [[Godiego]]||<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150809052153/http://news.dwango.jp/index.php?itemid=22502|title=EXILE USA\u7387\u3044\u308b\u300cDANCE EARTH PARTY\u300d\u65b0\u66f2\u306f\u30b4\u30c0\u30a4\u30b4\u306e\u540d\u66f2\u30ab\u30d0\u30fc \u00bb \u30c9\u30ef\u30f3\u30b4\u30b8\u30a7\u30a4\u30d4\u30fcnews - \u5171\u6709\u3059\u308b\u97f3\u697d\u60c5\u5831|date=2015-08-09|website=web.archive.org|access-date=2019-09-13}}</ref>\n|-\n|Very Special\n|[[Crystal Kay]]\n|''Shine''\n|Cover by  [[Debra Laws]]\n|\n|-\n|2016\n|FOREVER YOUNG AT HEART\n|Ryuji Imaichi\n|HiGH & LOW ORIGINAL BEST ALBUM\n|\n|<ref name=\":3\" />\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |2017\n|P.B.E.\n|[[Jay'ed|JAY'ED]]\n|''Here I Stand''\n|\n|\n|-\n|No more cry\n|[[Elly (dancer)|CrazyBoy]]\n|''NEOTOKYO FOREVER''\n|\n|\n|}\n\n=== Video releases ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Title\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Details\n! colspan=\"2\" |Peak Chart Positions\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Certifications\n|-\n![[Oricon|JPN]]\n[[Oricon|DVD]]\n![[Oricon|JPN]]\n[[Oricon|BD]]\n|-\n|RYUJI IMAICHI LIVE TOUR 2018 \"LIGHT>DARKNESS\"\n|\n* Released: March 6, 2019\n* Label: [[Rhythm Zone]]\n* Formats: 2DVD/CD, 2Blu-ray/CD\n|TBA\n|TBA\n|TBA\n|}\n\n=== Lyrics ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Year\n! Title\n! Artist\n! Recording\n! Notes\n|-\n|2014\n| PRIDE || rowspan=\"6\" |[[Sandaime J Soul Brothers from Exile Tribe]]||''[[The Best/Blue Impact]]''||\n|-\n|2015\n| ALL LOVE ||''[[Planet Seven]]''||\n|-\n|2016\n|Born in the EXILE\n|''The JSB Legacy''\n|\n|-\n|2017\n|HAPPY\n|''FUTURE''\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |2019\n|Yes We Are\n|\n|\n|-\n|Hanauta ~Flowers for you~\n|\n|\n|}\n== Tie-ups ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Title\n! Notes\n! Recording\n|-\n| All Love || Theme song for the [[TV Tokyo]] drama, ''Kuroi Gash\u016b: Kusa''||''Planet Seven''\n|-\n|RILY\n|Theme song for the AOYAMA PRESTIGE TECHNOLOGY CM 2019\n|''Zone of Gold''\n|-\n|Church by the sea\n|Title song of the short film ''Cinema Fighters Project \"On The Way\"''\n|\n|}\n==Filmography==\n\n===TV programmes===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Year\n!Title\n!Network\n!Notes\n|-\n|2012\n|''Ex-Lounge''\n|[[Tokyo Broadcasting System|TBS]]\n|\n|-\n|2017\n|''Love or Not\u266a''\n|dTV\u00d7FOD\n|MC\n|}\n\n=== TV Dramas ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Year\n!Title\n!Role\n!Network\n!Notes\n!Ref.\n|-\n|2016\n|[[:ja:\u30ca\u30a4\u30c8\u30d2\u30fc\u30ed\u30fc NAOTO|Night Hero NAOTO]]\n|Himself\n|[[TV Tokyo]]\n|Episode 1, 4, 9\n|\n|}\n\n=== Short film ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Year\n!Title\n!Role\n!Ref.\n|-\n|2019\n|Cinema Fighters Project \"''On The Way''\"\n|Kenta\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ldh.co.jp/news/detail.php?lang=eng&site=EXILE&newsid=0000019587|title=All the details of all the five works in \"CINEMA FIGHTERS project Part 3\" unveiled! {{!}} LDH - LOVE + DREAM + HAPPINESS TO THE WORLD -|website=www.ldh.co.jp|access-date=2019-06-22}}</ref>\n|