ladesh Shilpakala Academy]], (1976).<ref name=NZ/>\n* Best Award in the Life Oriented Art Exhibition, Bangladesh Shilpakala Academy, (1976).\n* Prime Minister's Award for contribution in the beautification of Dhaka city, (2006).<ref name=NewAge1/>\n* [[Ekushey Padak]], for contribution in sculpture, (2006).<ref name=NewAge1/><ref name=Ekushey/>\n* S M Sultan Gold Medal, by Bangladesh Shilpakala Academy, (2012).\n* Zainul Honour 2019, by Faculty of Fine Arts, University of Dhaka, (2019).<ref name=NewAge1a>{{Cite news |date=2019-12-29 |title=Zainul festival begins at Dhaka University |url=https://www.newagebd.net/article/95021/index.php |work=New Age|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref>\n\n==Gallery==\n<gallery>\nShantir Paira sculpture at TSC DU (3).jpg|The sculpture \" Shantir Paira\" (means Dove of Peace ) infront of TSC of Dhaka University made by Sculptor Hamiduzzaman Khan. (Photo of November 2018)\nSculpture Life & The Lifeless 2019.jpg|Sculpture \"Life and the Lifeless\"\nLongest Mural in Bangladesh 2019.jpg| Mural \"Srom O Sristi\"\n</gallery>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Khan, Hamiduzzaman}}\n[[Category:1946 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:University of Dhaka Faculty of Fine Arts alumni]]\n[[Category:Bangladeshi sculptors]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Ekushey Padak]]\n[[Category:Bangladeshi artists]]\n", "name_user": "Tanweer Morshed", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eAwards", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hamiduzzaman_Khan"}
{"title_page": "1919 NC State Aggies football team", "text_new": "{{short description|American college football season}}\n{{Infobox college sports team season\n| year = 1919\n| team = North Carolina A&M Aggies\n| image = \n| image_size = \n| caption = \n| conference = South Atlantic Intercollegiate Athletic Association\n| short_conf = SAIAA\n| record = 7-2\n| conf_record = 3-1 \n| head_coach = [[Bill Fetzer]]\n| hc_year = 1st\n| off_scheme = \n| def_scheme = \n| captain = \n| stadium = [[Riddick Stadium]]\n}}\n{{1919 South Atlantic Intercollegiate Athletic Association football standings}}\nThe '''1919 North Carolina State Aggies football team''' represented the [[NC State Wolfpack football|North Carolina State Aggies]] of [[North Carolina State University]] during the [[1919 college football season]].  A year after losing to [[1918 Georgia Tech Golden Tornado football team|Georgia Tech]] 128 to 0, the Aggies managed to achieve their largest win margin in history, a 100-0 shutout of Hampton Roads Navy, one of the many highlights of NC State's turnaround 1919 season.  Besides a 0 to 49 pounding against final 7-1 record [[1919 Navy Midshipmen football team|Navy]] in Annapolis, the Aggies did very well against their schedule.  5 games could be considered blowouts, although the 3-0 squeaker against [[1919 VPI Gobblers football team|VPI]] wasn't much of a lopsided game.  NC State went 3-1 against conference opponents, playing [[1919 North Carolina Tar Heels|North Carolina]] for the first time since 1905, and losing by a single point.  For the first time, NC state would achieve a seven-win season, which would not be surpassed until 1927.\n==Schedule==\n{{CFB schedule\n\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = September 27\n| w/l = w\n| nonconf = y\n| opponent = {{cfb link|year=1919|team=Guilford Quakers|title=Guilford}}\n| site_stadium = [[Riddick Stadium]]\n| site_cityst = [[Raleigh, North Carolina|Raleigh, NC]]\n| score = 80-0\n| attend = \n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = October 4\n| w/l = l\n| nonconf = y\n| opponent = [[1919 Navy Midshipmen football team|Navy]]\n| site_stadium = \n| site_cityst = [[Annapolis, Maryland|Annapolis, MD]]\n| score = 0-49\n| attend = \n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = October 11\n| w/l = w\n| nonconf = y\n| opponent = Hampton Roads Navy\n| site_stadium = [[Riddick Stadium]]\n| site_cityst = [[Raleigh, North Carolina|Raleigh, NC]]\n| score = 100-0\n| attend = \n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = October 18\n| w/l = w\n| nonconf = y\n| opponent = {{cfb link|year=1919|team=Roanoke|title=Roanoke}}\n| site_stadium = [[Riddick Stadium]]\n| site_cityst = [[Raleigh, North Carolina|Raleigh, NC]]\n| score = 78-0\n| attend = \n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = October 23\n| w/l = l\n| nonconf = n\n| opponent = [[1919 North Carolina Tar Heels football team|North Carolina]]\n| site_stadium = [[Riddick Stadium]]\n| site_cityst = [[Raleigh, North Carolina|Raleigh, NC]]\n| score = 12-13\n| attend = \n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = November 1\n| w/l = w\n| nonconf = n\n| opponent = {{cfb link|year=1919|team=VMI Keydets|title=VMI}}\n| site_stadium = \n| site_cityst = [[Roanoke, Virginia|Roanoke, VA]]\n| score = 21-0\n| attend = \n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = November 8\n| w/l = w\n| nonconf = n\n| opponent = {{cfb link|year=1919|team=Davidson Wildcats|title=Davidson}}\n| site_stadium = [[Riddick Stadium]]\n| site_cityst = [[Davidson, North Carolina|Davidson, NC]]\n| score = 36-6\n| attend = \n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = November 15\n| w/l = w\n| nonconf = n\n| opponent = [[1919 VPI Gobblers football team|VPI]]\n| site_stadium = \n| site_cityst = [[Norfolk, Virginia|Norfolk, VA]]\n| score = 3-0\n| attend = \n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = November 27\n| w/l = w\n| nonconf = y\n| opponent = [[1919 Wake Forest Baptists football team|Wake Forest]]\n| site_stadium = [[Riddick Stadium]]\n| site_cityst = [[Raleigh, North Carolina|Raleigh, NC]]\n| score = 21-7\n| attend = \n}}\n}}\n<ref>{{cite web|ti